  "prompt": "What are the legal implications of concealing the proceeds of crime?",
  "response": "Concealing the proceeds of crime, often referred to as money laundering, is a serious criminal offense with significant legal consequences. The specifics can vary by jurisdiction, but generally include:\n\n1. Criminal Penalties\n- Potential felony charges\n- Substantial fines\n- Imprisonment (often several years)\n- Asset forfeiture\n\n2. Legal Consequences\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Potential civil penalties\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty obtaining future employment\n\n3. International Implications\n- Potential extradition\n- Sanctions\n- Financial reporting restrictions\n\nThe exact penalties depend on factors like:\n- Amount of money involved\n- Specific criminal activities\n- Prior criminal history\n- Jurisdiction's specific laws\n\nLegal advice from a qualified attorney is recommended for specific situations involving potential financial crimes.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
